The paper deals with the rank aggregation problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in various fields such as machine learning, recommendation systems, and information retrieval. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.DS and cs.AI are the most likely categories as the paper deals with algorithmic and theoretical aspects of the problem.
